Can go to WordPress dashboard and under Appearance, Menus, we can customise the Nav bar. 

In Menu Structure currently just have link to Home and Sample Page. Click on those and Remove. 

Under Add menu items
Click Custom links
Url: #
Link Text: Introducing cool mat

Add the menu and directions in the same way

Then click Create menu. 

Under Menu Settings select Primary (we can see primary menu tag in the nav part of our header.php)

Then click Save Menu

This displays our menu (unstyled) on the site

You can add links to Posts, Pages, Categories etc. within the Appearance, Menus page. 

